      "note": "Six Days: see n. 1031, to 7:54. The \"Day\" does not mean a day as we reckon it, viz.: one apparent course of the sun round the earth, for it refers to conditions which began before the earth and the sun were created. In verse 5 below, a Day is compared to a thousand years of our reckoning, and in 70:4 to 50,000 years. These figures \"as we reckon\" have no relation to \"timeless Time\", and must be taken to mean very long Periods, or Ages, or Aeons. See further 41:9-12, and notes."
